org.knime.core.data.container

Interface CellFactory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCellFactory, AbstractMany2OneCellFactory, AbstractMany2OneCellFactory, AggregationCellFactory, BasisFunctionPredictor2CellFactory, BasisFunctionPredictorCellFactory, BinaryCellFactory, BinaryCellFactory, BinnerColumnFactory, BinnerColumnFactory, BinningCellFactory, BitString2BitVectorCellFactory, BitVectorCellFactory, BitVectorColumnCellFactory, CategoryToNumberApplyCellFactory, CategoryToNumberCellFactory, CategoryToNumberCellFactory, CellSplitterByPosCellFactory, CellSplitterCellFactory, ClusterMembershipFactory, Collection2BitVectorCellFactory, ColumnRearranger.DataCellTypeConverterCellFactory, Hex2BitVectorCellFactory, IdString2BitVectorCellFactory, LinReg2Predictor, LogRegPredictor, MDSCellFactory, MinMaxCellFactory, MinMaxCellFactory, MultiString2BitVectorCellFactory, NaiveBayesCellFactory, NaiveBayesCellFactory, NaiveBayesCellFactory, NumberToCategoryApplyCellFactory, Numeric2BitVectorMeanCellFactory, Numeric2BitVectorThresholdCellFactory, One2ManyCellFactory, One2ManyCellFactory, RankCellFactory, RegExpCellFactory, RegExpCellFactory, RegressionPredictorCellFactory, RoundDoubleCellFactory, SingleCellFactory, SotaPredictorCellFactory, SplitCellFactory, SVMPredictor, SVMPredictor

    public interface CellFactory
    Factory for a ColumnRearranger to provide new columns which are, e.g. appended to a given table.

    Note, it's strongly recommend to extend the abstract classes AbstractCellFactory and SingleCellFactory instead of implementing this interface. These classes also enable the parallel processing of the input table and access to a FileStoreFactory.

    Author:
    Bernd Wiswedel, University of Konstanz
    See Also:
    ColumnRearranger, ColumnRearranger.append(CellFactory)
    No public API: not to be implemented by clients
    This interface is not intended to be implemented by clients, use AbstractCellFactory or SingleCellFactory instead

    • Method Detail

      • getCells

        DataCell[] getCells(DataRow row)
        Get the new cells for a given row. These cells are incorporated into the existing row. The way it is done is defined through the ColumnRearranger using this object.
        Parameters:
        row - The row of interest.
        Returns:
        The new cells to that row.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If there is no mapping available.

      • getColumnSpecs

        DataColumnSpec[] getColumnSpecs()
        The column specs for the cells that are generated in the getCells() method. This method is only called once, there is no need to cache the return value. The length of the returned array must match the length of the array returned by the getCells(DataRow) method and also the types must match, i.e. the type of the respective DataColumnSpec must be of the same type or a super type of the cell as returned by getCells(DataRow).
        Returns:
        The specs to the newly created cells.

      • setProgress

        @Deprecated
void setProgress(int curRowNr,
                             int rowCount,
                             RowKey lastKey,
                             ExecutionMonitor exec)
        Deprecated. use/implement setProgress(long, long, RowKey, ExecutionMonitor) instead which supports more than Integer.MAX_VALUE rows
        This method is called when a row has been processed. It allows the implementor to set progress in the execution monitor and also some meaningful progress message.

        Note, you don't need to check exec.checkCanceled() in the implementation as this is done in the calling class.

        Parameters:
        curRowNr - The number of the row just processed
        rowCount - The total number of rows.
        lastKey - The row's key.
        exec - The execution monitor to report progress to.
